instruction_original:
```
import * as THREE from 'three';

// Define the geometry of the house
const geometry = new THREE.BoxGeometry(10, 10, 10);

// Define the material of the house
const material = new THREE.MeshLambertMaterial({ color: 0x00ff00 });

// Create the house object
const house = new THREE.Mesh(geometry, material);

// Add the house to the scene
scene.add(house);

// Render the scene
function render() {
  requestAnimationFrame(render);

  // Render the scene
  renderer.render(scene, camera);
}

// Initialize the renderer and the scene
const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer();
renderer.setSize(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight);
document.body.appendChild(renderer.domElement);

// Initialize the scene
const scene = new THREE.Scene();

// Render the house
render();
```

**Instructions:**

1. Save the code above as a file named `house.js`.
2. Open the file in a web browser.
3. Resize the window to see the house.

**Notes:**

* The house

